\title{anansi: Consensus/Discrepancy Visualization for Sets of Phylogenetic Networks}
\description{
anansi overlays a \emph{set} of explicit reticulate phylogenetic networks
(extended Newick / \link[ape:evonet]{ape::evonet}) over a fixed taxon set in a DensiTree-style
consensus/discrepancy view: networks are drawn on a shared tip ordering with
alpha transparency so that agreement appears dense and conflict appears
diffuse. Backbone-tree topology and reticulation-edge placement are shown
together, and all networks can be restricted to a subset of taxa.
}
\details{
The package is organized as a small framework:
\itemize{
\item I/O & data model (\code{io.R}, \code{netset.R}) -- read networks and build a
validated \code{anansi_netset}.
\item Layout engine (\code{layout.R}) -- compute a shared coordinate frame.
\item Consensus (\code{consensus.R}) -- clade and reticulation-event frequencies.
\item Plotting (\code{plot.R}, \code{discrepancy.R}) -- the \code{densinet()} overlay.
\item Taxa (\code{taxa.R}) -- restrict networks to a subset of taxa.
}

See \code{docs/DESIGN.md} for design decisions and \code{docs/WORKPLAN.md} for the
phased roadmap and feature-status tracker.
